Graduate Trainee Responsibilities:

As a graduate trainee, your responsibilities include

  •  Shadowing various team members
  •  Participating in learning experiences
  •  Understand various environments (development, testing, pre-production and production) to gain practical experience.
  •  To be successful as a graduate trainee, you should be willing to learn about aspects of the company that lie outside of your department/team.
  •  An outstanding graduate trainee should foster good relationships with staff members and leave a lasting imprint.
  •  Participate in training exercises, meetings, workshops, and team-building events.
  •  Preparing quality documents as part of the learning experiences and keeping a log of things learned.
  •  Compiling reports and making presentations to other staff members.
  •  Analyzing existing processes and systems and offer new ideas as part of continual service improvement.
  •  Bringing positive energy into the company and forming lasting professional relationships with staff.
  •  Collect data, analyze and present it in the required form by assisting the Manager or Supervisor wherever possible.
  •  Be a CDK ambassador at all times.
  •  Complete an internal evaluation at the end of the graduate program.

  •  Engineering Degree in the relevant field. 
  •  Excellent written and verbal communication skills.
  •  Good Listening skills and should be collaborative.
  •  Excellent research abilities and a willingness to grow.
  •  A positive attitude and a growth mindset.
  •  Appetite for learning.
  •  Ability to work under pressure and manage/resolve issues promptly.
  •  Willingness to work in a 24/7 environment.
  •  Exposure to Object Oriented Programming concepts and familiarity in any programming language (Ex. Python, Java).

Ultimately, you will become an infrastructure engineer primarily focusing on the up-keep and availability of our virtualization, hyper converged  cloud infrastructure. You will be trained to work on operational activities to maintain the health and recovery our IT Infrastructure from any failures. You will be engaging with multiple stakeholders across the business.

Job summary
Amazon strives to delight customers and make their lives easier. We have an extensive range of opportunities to learn and experiment to grow under the guidance of a pioneer engineering community. We are looking for you if you are a highly determined/motivated engineer who loves challenges and commits to improvement every day. Our Support Engineers get exposure to disruptive technologies applied in our software solutions. They collaborate with software development teams to raise the engineering and operational excellence to define the future.

 

 

Key job responsibilities
As a Support Engineer you will:
Play vital role in helping us leverage supporting and developing technologies on any platform to increase global collaboration, increase efficiency, and meet our controller ship requirements
Directly work with development teams to improve the applications built by conducting technical mitigations and deep dives on reported issues to find the cause and corrective actions.
Work with our other technical teams to ensure the design is effective and complements of our in house custom developed applications across platform stacks (including SQL, Java/.NET/C#/Perl/Python) or SaaS.
Work on proactive detection mechanism to report dip in software performance by building efficient metrics/monitors/alarms using our in house tools.
Build tools and automations to optimize the system, simplify processes, etc.

 

 

PREFERRED QUALIFICATIONS

Experience in applications development would be an added advantage
Experience in supporting services that use AWS
Have the ability to learn technical concepts quickly with a strong sense of urgency
Have enthusiasm for working in a fast paced, rapidly changing environment
Be a creative problem solver, who is passionate about innovation and customer experience
Have strong written and oral communication skills
Capable to deal with ambiguity; work with minimum supervision
